# Get Authors

This endpoint retrieves a list of authors.

## Request

- Method: GET

- URL: localhost:8000/api/v1/authors


## Response

The response will be a JSON object with a `data` array containing author information. Each author object in the array will have the following attributes:

- `id` (string): The unique identifier of the author.

- `type` (string): The type of the author.

- `attributes` (object): An object containing the following attributes:

    - `name` (string): The name of the author.

    - `created_at` (string): The timestamp when the author was created.

    - `updated_at` (string): The timestamp when the author was last updated.


### JSON Schema

``` json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "data": {
      "type": "array",
      "items": {
        "type": "object",
        "properties": {
          "id": { "type": "string" },
          "type": { "type": "string" },
          "attributes": {
            "type": "object",
            "properties": {
              "name": { "type": "string" },
              "created_at": { "type": "string" },
              "updated_at": { "type": "string" }
            }
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}

 ```

